place.name: BEXWELL
place.gazetteerText: BEXWELL, a parish in Downham district, Norfolk; 1 mile E of Downham-Market r. station. Post Town, Downham. Acres, 1,177. Real property, £2,075. Pop., 94. Houses, 16. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £375.* Patron, the Bishop of Norwich. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
